#If the bill was $150.00, split between 5 people, with 12% tip. 

#Each person should pay (150.00 / 5) * 1.12 = 33.6
#Format the result to 2 decimal places = 33.60

#Tip: There are 2 ways to round a number. You might have to do some Googling to solve this.ðŸ’ª

#Write your code below this line ðŸ‘‡
print("Welcome to my Tip Calculator!")
totalBill = input("What was the total bill?\n$")
tipPercentage = input("What percent tip would you like to give?\n")
people = input("How many people will be splitting this bill?\n")
bill = float(totalBill)
tip = float(float(totalBill)*(int(tipPercentage)/100))
pay = round((bill + tip)/int(people),2)
print(f"Each person pays ${pay}")
